<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: FABCO SDA-12 - LUBRICATION - KING PIN BEARINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>KING PIN BEARINGS</title>
        <para>Kingpin bearings should be lubricated at each chassis lubrication (approximately 1,000 mile intervals). To
            ensure thorough lubrication, the front axle should be raised slightly to relieve weight. The lower kingpin
            lube fitting is located in the lower kingpin bearing plate and is accessible in the top surface of the lower
            arm of the suspension yoke (refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0201046">Figure 46</hotlnk>). The upper king- pin fitting is either on the front or rear of
            the upper kingpin bracket (refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0201046">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0201046" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201046.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 46. Lubrication Points</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. UNIVERSAL JOINT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. UPPER KING PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>3. GREASE FITTING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. TIE ROD ENDS</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LOWER KING PIN</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
